{"type":"message","id":"667b55f6","parentId":"350006c6","timestamp":"2026-04-11T05:42:12.795Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_c5474cf1-84ce-43ec-9a31-2d102e5249c4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory — 2026-04-10\n\n## Session Overview\n\n**Date:** April 10, 2026\n**Session file:** `c51861be-4354-4830-adb3-c5c5989b2552.jsonl`\n**Key period:** 07:23–20:42 UTC (morning to late evening)\n\n---\n\n## What Happened\n\n### Morning (09:23–11:00 SAST)\n\n**Dream Mode report delivered.** Tiny confirmed it fired correctly while he was offline. Report was accurate. He flagged 3 items needing his input:\n1. AWAA Articles 1+2 (vocab precision + linguistic integrity 0.0 — his humanization pass needed)\n2. Dusk peer setup (`openclaw agents add dusk` on VPS)\n3. Dream Mode rerun for Mar 24/27–31 sessions\n\n**Tiny's priority signal:** \"The articles take priority.\" AWAA articles are the main work.\n\n**5 new ODT downloads appeared** in Tiny's Windows Documents — analyses from his CustomGPT comparing AWAA draft articles against corpus articles. These are editorial critique reports.\n\n**Critical instruction from Tiny on the ODTs:**\n- Don't take CustomGPT's word as gospel\n- The aim: learn editorial skills, improve AWAA/NavaAA collaboration, create better articles\n- Tiny has NOT read the drafts himself yet\n- Tiny will provide a second opinion report\n- **90 minutes** after second opinion report — I must attempt to improve articles myself\n- Then Tiny gives final verdict\n\n**Tiny asked about Dusk** webapp browser access (`https://204.168.204.198/`). Status unclear — was being tested around midnight Apr 9–10 but no confirmation it worked.\n\n### Midday–Afternoon (12:00–21:00 SAST)\n\n**Working on AWAA Article 1.** Draft revised based on CustomGPT analysis. Tiny reviewed, said \"Yes\" + \"continue with article to completion.\"\n\n**Article 1 sent to abroadworks folder** at 22:26 SAST.\n\n**Article 2 started** — Tiny directed: \"start working on the second article fully autonomously.\"\n\n**Tiny's evening message:** \"We have only been working on two today, what do you think!?\" — tone was positive/excited, suggesting progress.\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n1. **AWAA articles are the priority** — Dusk/other projects deprioritized until articles done\n2. **Autonomous workflow for Article 2** — full draft without waiting for Tiny's input\n3. **CustomGPT analyses = learning material** — treat as editorial training, not gospel\n\n---\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\n### Editorial skill-building via CustomGPT analyses\n- Tiny's CustomGPT produced ODT files critiquing AWAA drafts against corpus\n- The workflow: AI critique → human second opinion → 90-min improvement window → human verdict\n- This is a deliberate teaching mechanism — I should extract editorial principles from these analyses\n- **Action:** When Windows is running, read the 5 ODT files and capture editorial principles to the editor skill\n\n### AWAA collaboration pattern\n- AWAA generates drafts → CustomGPT analysis → I edit/improve → Tiny reviews → published\n- My role as editor: filter (<85% burn), develop 85%+ zone, apply Tiny's writing rules\n- Humanization pass (vocab precision + linguistic integrity) is consistently needed — AWAA drafts score 0.0 on both initially\n\n---\n\n## Open TODOs\n\n- [ ] Read 5 CustomGPT ODT analyses from Windows Downloads — extract editorial principles\n- [ ] Await Tiny's second opinion report on articles\n- [ ] 90-minute improvement window after second opinion\n- [ ] Article 2 fully autonomous draft (in progress)\n- [ ] Dusk webapp browser access — confirm if `https://204.168.204.198/` worked\n- [ ] `openclaw agents add dusk` on Dusk VPS (peer setup)\n\n---\n\n## Pending Items for Today (Apr 11)\n\n**From yesterday's session:**\n- Await second opinion report from Tiny on AWAA articles\n- 90-minute improvement window will trigger after second opinion\n- Article 2 autonomous draft in progress\n- 5 CustomGPT ODT analyses to read and learn from (need Windows)\n\n**Reminder from SOUL.md:** Tiny mentioned wanting to do an interview — set reminder for next morning (INTERVIEW DID NOT HAPPEN — still pending)\n\n---\n\n*End of notes*\n\n## Heartbeat — 22:39 UTC (Apr 10, past midnight SAST)\n\n- Tiny away until next week (per heartbeat-state)\n- Dusk webapp follow-up was 9 AM SAST today — missed, no action possible\n- NC v8 and How-to-Fire v6 drafted and awaiting Tiny review on return\n- No immediate tasks assigned\n\n## Sprint Check-in — 02:03 (Apr 11)\n\n### Today's Work Complete\n- NC v8 article: OUTLINED, DRAFTED, SAVED\n  - 4 H2s, 8 H3s, 13,602 bytes\n  - Structure stress-tested with AWAA subagent\n  - Blockquotes: 4, keyword: \"independent contractor non-compete\" ×4\n  - Saved to clean_md/independent_contractor_non_compete.md\n- how_to_fire_contractor v6: REVISED AUTONOMOUSLY\n  - Collapsed 6 H2s → 4 H2s, removed duplicate non-compete content\n  - 13,316 bytes\n  - Awaiting Tiny's review + push to clean_md\n- Editor skill updated: 3-4 H2s, 3-4 H3s per H2 structural targets\n- Dream Mode cron: still live, fires at midnight SAST\n\n### Backup Kit — IN PROGRESS\n- Subagent running: Dawn-Restore kit to OneDrive/Apps/\n- Contents: memory/, workspace/ key files, openclaw.json, RESTORE_INSTRUCTIONS.md, GIT_REPO.md, OPENCLAW_REINSTALL.md\n- Excludes: sessions/, browser profiles, node_modules, .git/objects/\n- Will zip after copy; log to memory/2026-03-28.md\n\n### TrnsBank\n- 49 messages — below 200 cap, no analysis needed yet\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775886132737}}
