age.org/leadingage-reax-repeal-of-nursing-home-minimum-staffing-standards/","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775887288217}}
{"type":"message","id":"d1b9b2c0","parentId":"1876f16c","timestamp":"2026-04-11T06:01:28.278Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_fa07825a-a314-40cb-9db3-cf61733f6930","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Post 3 — Nava Healthcare Corporate\n**Date:** April 9, 2026\n**Status:** READY TO PUBLISH\n**Topic:** Continuity / Merry-Go-Rounds\n\n---\n\nA travelling nurse reaches week seven of their contract and finally understands the culture and where the best karaoke in town is. Week nine, they've started anticipating which physicians prefer which workflows.\n\nThen week thirteen arrives, and they leave.\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗵𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀 𝗹𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝗰𝗸𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸, but not because nurses want to leave. Some negotiate to come back. Some choose their next contract carefully. But many leave because this is how to make a living in this industry.\n\nThe 13-week reset is a structural feature of the travel staffing model. Agencies profit on volume: new placements, new contracts, new orientation gaps. A nurse who knows your unit intimately is a nurse who's harder to place. Familiarity breeds comfort, and places unknown come with uncertainty and social anxiety. So the system moves them before they feel at home.\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝘂𝗻𝗶𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘆𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲: hand-off errors, orientation costs, the institutional knowledge that never accumulates because it keeps walking out the door.\n\nWe built Nava differently. Continuity requires someone who stays, so we structure around that from day one:\n • Truth at placement,\n • Follow-up after arrival,\n • Relationships that outlast the contract cycle.\n\n𝗕𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝘄𝗲 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗱𝗲𝗮𝗹 𝗶𝗻 𝟭𝟯-𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸 𝗺𝗲𝗿𝗿𝘆-𝗴𝗼-𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱𝘀.\n\nIf you're tired of funding the learning curve, let's talk.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775887288243}}
{"type":"message","id":"a16fbe46","parentId":"d1b9b2c0","timestamp":"2026-04-11T06:01:39.746Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[[reply_to_current]] **Morning Brief — Sat 11 Apr, 08:00**\n\n**Confirmed priorities (from yesterday + yesterday's pending tasks):**\n\n**1. Abroadworks articles** ✅ — both now in `/abroadworks/`:\n   - `article-independent-contractor-non-compete.md`\n   - `article-how-to-fire-an-independent-contractor.md`\n   \n   What's the publish step? Do I push to the site or do you handle that?\n\n**2. Nava Post 3 (ready to publish)**\n   Found the draft — `li-post3-2026-04-09.md` in drafts folder. Topic: **the 13-week merry-go-round** — travel nurse model resets before institutional knowledge builds. Nava's differentiator: continuity over placement volume.\n   \n   1 tweet or thread format? And which Nava page — corporate or your personal?\n\n**3. EB-3 vs TN lawyer corrections**\n   The file `TN - FR EDits.docx` isn't showing in Downloads. Could the filename be slightly different? I can scan for it if you want.\n\n**4. OpenClaw reinstall** — noted, not a priority right now. Holding.\n\nWhat's the publish order — articles first, then Nava Post 3?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":39853,"output":545,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40398,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775887299745}}
