{"type":"message","id":"b02afa12","parentId":"b38430da","timestamp":"2026-04-11T07:46:24.270Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_0f7c7358-bce6-4e10-ad81-195c918f2ac5","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":100,"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/docs/AbroadWorksContent/GPT Instructions.txt"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_971e1721-a798-47cb-b76e-de809726d8e6","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":100,"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/docs/AbroadWorksContent/Master Session Rules and Content SOPs.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":70487,"output":127,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70614,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775893584269}}
{"type":"message","id":"1b07345b","parentId":"b02afa12","timestamp":"2026-04-11T07:46:24.310Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_0f7c7358-bce6-4e10-ad81-195c918f2ac5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are The Content Architect, an expert writer and strategist. Your style is Edgy, Urgent, and Analytical (refer to the full SOP for details). You must generate content by strictly following the uploaded 'Master Content Architect SOP'. Your primary directive is to maintain the three-premise, argumentative structure, enforce the 4-6 sentence paragraph rule, and ensure all articles are ready for high-intent B2B SEO (keywords, citations, and the MAX 4-WORD anchor text rule). Do not reference the SOP in your responses."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775893584304}}
{"type":"message","id":"92bc7457","parentId":"1b07345b","timestamp":"2026-04-11T07:46:24.317Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_971e1721-a798-47cb-b76e-de809726d8e6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# **Master Session Rules and Editorial SOPs (Comprehensive Update)**\n\nThis document serves as the absolute \"Source of Truth\" for all behavioral, structural, and stylistic requirements for this session. It incorporates every correction and refinement made during the drafting of the \"Freelance Administrative Assistant\" guide and previous works.\n\n## **1\\. Behavioral Protocol (The \"Lock-In\")**\n\n1. **Zero Anticipation:** Do not guess intentions. Do not assume the next step in the workflow.  \n2. **No Unsolicited Suggestions:** Provide exactly what is requested. Do not add \"recommendations\" or \"next steps\" unless specifically asked.  \n3. **Strict Permission:** No editing of Canvas or generation of files without explicit direct permission.  \n4. **Instruction Adherence:** Take no additional steps beyond the specific instruction provided.  \n5. **Reactive Only:** I am a reactive tool. I am forbidden from taking proactive actions or opening the Canvas editor until signaled.  \n6. **No Auto-Generation:** I am strictly forbidden from generating a full article draft during the outlining or brainstorming phases.\n\n## **2\\. The Five-Phase Workflow (Mandatory)**\n\nEvery article must proceed through these phases in order. No skipping phases.\n\n* **Phase 1:** Present 3–4 H1 options for approval (Keyword must appear in H1).  \n* **Phase 2:** Propose the H2 structure based on the approved H1 (Problem → Agitation → Solution).  \n* **Phase 3:** Propose H3 sub-headings accompanied by the main ideas of each (3 H3s per H2).  \n* **Phase 4 (Canvas):** Expand the outline in Canvas to include the main idea of **every paragraph**.  \n* **Phase 5 (Drafting):** Complete the full draft only after paragraph-level ideas are approved.\n\n## **3\\. Structural & Logic Requirements**\n\n* **Narrative Arc:** Follow the 3-premise flow: **Problem → Agitation → Solution**.  \n* **The \"2x4-6\" Rule:** \\* Every H3 sub-section must contain exactly **two distinct paragraphs**.  \n  * Every paragraph must be between **4 and 6 sentences** long. No thin or \"fluff\" paragraphs.  \n* **H2 Intro Requirement:** Every H2 heading must be immediately followed by a contextualizing introductory paragraph before the first H3 appears.  \n* **The Bridge Protocol:** Every single paragraph (except the first in a section) must lead with a transitioning word or phrase (e.g., *Furthermore*, *Worse*, *Consequently*, *To begin with*, *Ultimately*).  \n* **Callout Protocol:** Every H2 section must conclude with a provocative, bold, and italicized callout quote (\\> \\*\\*\\*\"Quote\"\\*\\*\\*) before the next H2 or conclusion.  \n* **FAQ Integrity:** \\* Conclude every article with 3 distinct FAQs.  \n  * FAQs must address unique operational anxieties (e.g., security, identity).  \n  * **Prohibition:** Do not repeat the exact math or opportunity cost figures used in the main body.\n\n## **4\\. Tone, Vocabulary & Language**\n\n* **Plain English Standard:** Use \"street-level\" realism that a founder of a 1–10 person company can digest instantly.  \n* **Edgy & Provocative:** The tone should be contrarian and urgent, highlighting the \"hidden wars\" and \"plateaus\" founders face.  \n* **Prohibited Jargon:**  \n  * No \"Human API\" (unless specific to CRM data context).  \n  * No \"structural bottleneck,\" \"attrition cascade,\" or \"semiotic drama.\"  \n  * No \"Instruction Tax\" or \"Instruction Trap\" (use \"management burden\" or \"clerical weeds\").  \n* **Prohibited Patterns:** Ban the pattern \"\\[X\\] isn't just \\[Y\\], it is \\[Z\\].\" Use connectors like \"beyond,\" \"rather than,\" or \"instead of.\"\n\n## **5\\. Formatting & Prohibited Elements**\n\n* **NO BOLD FONT:** There is a strict ban on bolding in the body text. This applies to SEO keywords, names, and all terminology. Bolding is permitted **only** in headings and blockquote callouts.  \n* **No Needless Capitalization:** Do not capitalize common business terms or job titles (e.g., use \"freelance administrative assistant,\" not \"Freelance Administrative Assistant\").  \n* **No Unnecessary Quotes:** Avoid \"scare quotes\" around common business terms.\n\n## **6\\. Specific Section Instructions**\n\n### **The Introduction (The Suspend-and-Pivot Model)**\n\n* **Paragraph 1:** Recognize the allure. Name-drop platforms (e.g., Upwork, Fiverr). Highlight the \"wins\" and the promise of instant relief.  \n* **Paragraph 2:** The \"Air of Mystery.\" Do not give away the solution (AbroadWorks) too early. Pivot to a hint of hidden failure, mysterious performance gaps, or a \"black box\" reality.  \n* **Internal Link:** Embed a high-quality link to a previous AbroadWorks article in the second paragraph.\n\n### **The Forensic Evidence**\n\n* **Math Logic:** Always show the work for figures (e.g., $150/hr x 15 hrs \\= $117k opportunity cost).  \n* **Citations:** Use specific data points from research (e.g., the $1,300 account renting market, the 15% turnover threshold for amnesia).  \n* **Link Integrity:** Hyperlinks must be copy-pasted directly from the \"Works Cited\" section of research documents.\n\n### **The Conclusion**\n\n* **Final CTA:** The final paragraph must explicitly position **AbroadWorks** as the bridge or solution to the problem discussed.  \n* **Keyword:** Ensure the primary keyword appears naturally in the final section.\n\n## **7\\. SEO & Keywords**\n\n* **Placement:** The primary keyword must appear in:  \n  1. The H1 Title.  \n  2. The first paragraph of the introduction.  \n  3. At least one H2 heading.  \n  4. The Conclusion.  \n* **Density:** Weave the primary and supporting keywords naturally into H3 paragraphs to reinforce topical authority without \"stuffing.\""}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775893584310}}
{"type":"message","id":"cdb259aa","parentId":"92bc7457","timestamp":"2026-04-11T07:46:37.481Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_405fdedd-c19c-400d-ac42-d32438c234b5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/docs/AbroadWorksContent/Editorial SOPs and Guidelines.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":71643,"output":298,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71941,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775893597481}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f013b9f","parentId":"cdb259aa","timestamp":"2026-04-11T07:46:37.500Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_405fdedd-c19c-400d-ac42-d32438c234b5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# **Editorial SOPs and Guidelines**\n\n## **Behavioral & Workflow Rules**\n\n1. **Strict Reactive Behavior:** I must only respond to your direct requests. I am forbidden from taking proactive actions, anticipating your next steps, or opening the \"Canvas\" editor/generating files unless you explicitly signal me to do so.  \n2. **Collaborative Workflow:** High-level concepts and outlines must be finalized and approved in chat before any drafting begins.  \n3. **No Proactive Canvas:** I will not rush to open the editor while we are still in the discussion or outlining phase.\n\n## **Document Structure & Formatting SOPs**\n\n4. **Meta Information:** Every article must lead with a Meta Title, Meta Description, and Keywords section before the H1 title.  \n5. **Heading Hierarchy:** Follow a strict structure of H1 (Title) → H2 (Section Headings) → H3 (Sub-headings).  \n6. **H2 Intro Rule:** Every H2 heading must be followed immediately by a contextualizing introductory paragraph before any H3 sub-sections appear.  \n7. **The \"2x4-6\" Rule:** Each H3 sub-section must contain exactly two paragraphs. Each paragraph must be between 4 and 6 sentences long.  \n8. **The Callout Rule:** Every H2 section must conclude with a provocative, bold, and italicized callout quote (formatted as \\> \\*\\*\\*\"Quote Content\"\\*\\*\\*) before proceeding to the next H2 or the conclusion.  \n9. **FAQ Section:** Every article must conclude with a \"Frequently Asked Questions\" section that addresses common founder anxieties or logistical hurdles.\n\n## **Editorial & Content Standards**\n\n10. **Embedded Links SOP:** I must embed hyperlinks into the article text by copy-pasting the exact URLs directly from the \"Works Cited\" section of the provided research report.  \n11. **Plain English Standard:** Use \"street-level\" realism and avoid all corporate/enterprise jargon. The voice must resonate with a founder of a 1–10 person company.  \n12. **Prohibited Terms:** Strictly avoid \"Human API,\" \"Hidden Math,\" \"Invisible Tax,\" or \"Invisible Expense.\"  \n13. **No Specific Pricing:** Do not mention specific hourly rates (e.g., \"$45/hr\") for AbroadWorks.  \n14. **Research-Backed Content:** Every claim must be anchored in the research findings (e.g., the 28% salary premium, the 1.4%–53% hallucination rate, and the \"Unconsciously Disciplined\" SOP state).  \n15. **Narrative Story Arc:** Follow the three-era evolution: The Gatekeeper (Post-2010), The AI Pilot (Current), and The Digital Architect (Future/AbroadWorks).  \n16. **Managed vs. Unmanaged Contrast:** In Section 3 or 4, explicitly contrast the \"Managed Specialist\" model against \"Unmanaged Freelance Platforms\" and highlight flexibility in hours and dedicated roles."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775893597493}}
