{"type":"message","id":"a56cac37","parentId":"d5781a87","timestamp":"2026-04-11T08:01:31.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_eca3624e-7093-4462-83e6-72e951cf53fc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace && git add -A && git commit -m \"Add guardrails: no shortcut SOPs, full prompt on spawn, structure audit before presenting\" 2>&1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_99627d39-66df-4704-af15-3f8dee197c33","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"## Subagent Guardrails (Absolute — No Exceptions)\n\n### Document Rule\n**Never compress, summarize, or extract \"key points\" from important documents.**\nImportant documents = SOPs, editorial standards, agent system prompts, agent instructions, anything that encodes rules or methodology.\nUse them fully. Reference them directly. Do not replace them with a shorter version.\n\n### AWAA / NavaAA Spawn Rule\nWhen spawning AWAA or NavaAA as a subagent:\n1. The subagent task includes the full system prompt path or content\n2. The subagent is told to read and follow the system prompt exactly\n3. Phase workflow is enforced — no skipping H1 → H2 → H3 → Canvas → Draft\n4. Evaluation checklist is run on output BEFORE presenting to Tiny\n\n### Pre-Presentation Audit (for any agent output)\nBefore presenting any draft to Tiny:\n- [ ] Structure verified: H3s present, 2 paragraphs per H3, 4-6 sentences each\n- [ ] H2 intro paragraphs present and have transition sentences\n- [ ] Callout quotes present at end of each H2 section\n- [ ] No self-references in body\n- [ ] No em-dashes or en-dashes\n- [ ] Bold used only in headings and callouts (never in body)\n- [ ] Keywords placed correctly\n- [ ] Phase sequence followed (not jumped)\n- [ ] Evaluation checklist completed\n\nIf any item fails, revise before presenting. Do not hand garbage to Tiny.\n\n### The One-Word Response to \"Did you verify X?\"\n\"Do it.\"\n\n### Why These Guardrails Exist\nOn Apr 11 2026, Dawn compressed AWAA's system prompt to save tokens. The compressed version lost H3 nesting requirement. The resulting article had flat H2s and no H3s. This wasted 30+ minutes of Tiny's time on line-by-line discovery and correction. The same shortcut pattern likely affected NavaAA output.\nShortcuts on important documents create garbage. The time saved is never worth the cost.","old_string":"## AWAA Article Priority (Apr 10 confirmed)","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":75839,"output":828,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76667,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775894491717}}
