m fails, revise before presenting. Do not hand garbage to Tiny.\n+ 988 \n+ 989 ### The One-Word Response to \"Did you verify X?\"\n+ 990 \"Do it.\"\n+ 991 \n+ 992 ### Why These Guardrails Exist\n+ 993 On Apr 11 2026, Dawn compressed AWAA's system prompt to save tokens. The compressed version lost H3 nesting requirement. The resulting article had flat H2s and no H3s. This wasted 30+ minutes of Tiny's time on line-by-line discovery and correction. The same shortcut pattern likely affected NavaAA output.\n+ 994 Shortcuts on important documents create garbage. The time saved is never worth the cost.\n+ 995 \n  963 Tiny: \"The articles take priority.\" Dusk and other projects deprioritized until AWAA articles done.\n  964 \n  965 **Workflow:** AWAA generates → CustomGPT analysis → I edit/improve → Tiny reviews → published.\n  966 \n      ...","firstChangedLine":961},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775894492143}}
