IDE — genuine arguments FOR 13-week contracts:**\n\n- **Money is real.** Staff nurses report travelers earning $500+/week more on the same unit. One nurse posted: $3,100/week in NJ, which sounds good until you learn she pays $2,800/month rent. That's $40,300 per 13-week contract — real take-home.\n- **Flexibility is genuine.** Work a few months, take a month off. \"After one 13-week contract you're free to joi\n\n=== 46e65f89-15c7-42d0-959a-8c00ee540bbe.jsonl line 1747 ===\n# **The Structural and Financial Evolution of the 13-Week Travel Nurse Contract Model in U.S. Healthcare: A Comprehensive 2024–2026 Analysis**\n\nThe stabilization of the United States healthcare workforce in the mid-2020s has been defined by a fundamental transition from the \"crisis-driven\" labor market of the pandemic era to a more disciplined, albeit structurally dependent, reliance on the 13-week travel nurse contract model. As of 2026, healthcare staffing remains a structurally strong sector,\n\n=== 46e65f89-15c7-42d0-959a-8c00ee540bbe.jsonl line 1788 ===\nThe Structural and Financial Evolution of the 13-Week Travel Nurse Contract Model in U.S. Healthcare: A Comprehensive 2024–2026 Analysis The stabilization of the United States healthcare workforce in the mid-2020s has been defined by a fundamental transition from the &quot;crisis-driven&quot; labor market of the pandemic era to a more disciplined, albeit structurally dependent, reliance on the 13-week travel nurse contract model. As of 2026, healthcare staffing remains a structurally strong sect\n\n=== 81925542-1588-4cfc-8284-8adba71eb832.jsonl line 114 ===\nal code and pin trust via plugins.allow or install records (/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-web-search/index.ts)\\\\nOpenClaw status\\\\n\\\\nOverview\\\\n┌─────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\\\n│ Item            │ Value                                                                   