{"type":"compaction","id":"0f6de042","parentId":"af3926e9","timestamp":"2026-04-11T08:17:36.000Z","summary":"## Decisions\n## Decisions\n- **Root cause (confirmed):** AWAA contains H2/H3 structural rules but has no instruction to receive CustomGPT analysis and revise — CustomGPT (HumanizedGemini.html) exists only in Windows Downloads and is inaccessible to AWAA or editor from this environment\n- **Root cause (confirmed):** Editor was performing prose review but not catching structural failures (missing H3s) before presenting to Tiny — became a relay without structural audit responsibility\n- **Root cause (confirmed):** \"Based on CustomGPT\" claim was never implemented — AWAA's system prompt does not mention CustomGPT\n- **Decision pending:** Whether to encode CustomGPT's editorial principles directly into AWAA's system prompt so AWAA self-revises without an interpreter relay (Tiny must decide)\n- **Post 3 queue order:** Patient/LTC perspective (Post 4) deferred until Post 3 landed; Facility economics MSP/VMS frame (Post 5) deferred\n\n## Open TODOs\n- **[NEW - User Frustration]**: Update editor skill with H2/H3 structure lessons learned — Tiny explicitly requested this, expressed frustration it wasn't done previously\n- **[IN PROGRESS]**: Read and audit AWAA's actual H2/H3 structural rules encoding in detail (truncated in conversation)\n- **[IN PROGRESS]**: Assess whether CustomGPT's benchmark logic needs to be ported into AWAA's system prompt\n- **[IN PROGRESS]**: Confirm structural state of article file (`abroadworks/article-independent-contractor-non-compete.md`)\n- **[IN PROGRESS]**: Determine whether to encode CustomGPT's editorial principles directly into AWAA's system prompt\n- Regenerate article with proper H2+H3 nesting if structural audit fails\n- Continue line-by-line editorial review of `article-independent-contractor-non-compete.md` (P2 onward — P1 complete)\n- Apply edi\n\n[Compaction summary truncated to fit budget]\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\