-\n\n### H2.3 — What Actually Protects You\n\n**H3.3.1 — IP assignment: the foundation most agreements skip**\n*Main idea:* Copyright and IP assignment clauses directly transfer ownership of work product — code, designs, copy, funnels — to your business from the moment of creation. This is the mechanism that answers \"can they use what they built for me against me?\" Work made for hire applies in narrow cases; explicit assignment covers the broader ground.\n\n**H3.3.2 — Trade secret law: federal and state-robust, covers the information problem**\n*Main idea:* The Defend Trade Secrets Act and state UTSA laws protect confidential business information without requiring a contract clause at all. Client lists, pricing structures, internal processes, and proprietary methods are covered if you took reasonable steps to keep them confidential. This is the mechanism that answers \"can they take my customer knowledge?\"\n\n**H3.3.3 — Non-solicitation: the clause that actually targets client relationships**\n*Main idea:* A well-drafted client non-solicitation clause directly restricts your contractor from approaching your customers after the relationship ends. Unlike non-competes, courts have historically been more receptiv\n…(truncated)…"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","timestamp":1775895246339,"__openclaw":{"id":"d653225c","seq":6}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"H3 sub-headings confirmed. Proceed to Phase 4 — paragraph-level canvas expansion. For each H3, write the main idea of both paragraphs (2 per H3), following 2x4-6 rule. Wait for my approval before Phase 5."}],"timestamp":1775895288447,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:main:main","sourceChannel":"whatsapp","sourceTool":"sessions_send"},"__openclaw":{"id":"4d2c0844","seq":7}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## PHASE 4: Paragraph-Level Canvas\n\nTwo paragraphs per H3. Each paragraph states its full 