{"type":"message","id":"6a326533","parentId":"8e100943","timestamp":"2026-04-11T08:22:27.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Stop. You're right to hold me accountable — I was about to push you into reviewing a draft that has major structural problems I should have caught myself.\n\nLet me do my job. Reading the draft now with editorial eyes:\n\n**Problem 1 — H2s don't match approved outline:**\n\nThe approved H2.1 was **\"The Promise and the Gap.\"** The draft opens with **\"What a Non-Compete Actually Does.\"** That's not a minor wording difference — one frames it as a gap/promise disruption, the other frames it as a simple explainer. Different articles entirely.\n\n**Problem 2 — No H3s exist in the draft.** Zero. The 2x4-6 rule (each H3 = 2 paragraphs) is completely absent. The approved outline had 11 H3s across 4 sections. The draft has none.\n\n**Problem 3 — No H2 intro paragraphs.** The system prompt required every H2 to have a contextualizing intro before the first H3. The draft goes straight into body text.\n\n**Problem 4 — Only one callout quote.** System prompt requires one at the end of EVERY H2 section. Only H2.3 has one.\n\n**Problem 5 — FAQ uses wrong formatting.** Questions are bolded inline instead of using H3 tags per SOP.\n\n**My assessment:** This is not a line-by-line review problem. This is a structural rebuild. AWAA generated prose that ignores the outline it was given.\n\n**Two options:**\n\n1. **Send AWAA back to Phase 3** with the approved outline H2s and force it to build the proper H3 structure before any prose is written\n2. **I rebuild the structure manually** based on the approved outline, then we revise prose from there\n\nWhich do you want?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":64348,"output":1843,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66191,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":17758957478