{"type":"message","id":"10ebaa55","parentId":"eb9db0c4","timestamp":"2026-04-11T08:39:51.335Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes. Here's the full marker system as I understand it:\n\n| Marker | Who uses it | Meaning |\n|--------|-------------|---------|\n| `@t` | Me → Tiny | My message to you |\n| `@d` | Tiny → Me | Your message to me |\n| `@aw` | AWAA → Me | File complete notification |\n| `+27763674298` | WhatsApp | Your actual message (primary identifier) |\n| `gateway-client` | TUI | Your actual message |\n\nThe source metadata (`+27763674298`, `gateway-client`) is more reliable than the text markers — it's hardwired to the sender. I use it to route. The text markers are confirmatory.\n\nOne clarification: AWAA doesn't message you directly. It writes a file and tells me `[File written]: /path.md @aw`. I read the file and present to you. You then send feedback to me. I relay to AWAA. The loop is always: Tiny ↔ Me ↔ AWAA.\n\nThat's the architecture. Sounds viable.\n\nOne question: do you want AWAA's `@aw` notifications to come straight to you in this session, or do you want them to route through me first?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":48393,"output":573,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48966,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775896791334}}
