{"type":"message","id":"24e30d8c","parentId":"0eee6f6e","timestamp":"2026-04-11T09:23:32.877Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Honestly? I've been winging it.\n\nThe Phase 4 canvas tells AWAA *what* each paragraph must prove and *how* the argument flows, sentence by sentence. But there's no skill for actually executing the prose from that canvas. AWAA gets the canvas instructions and is told to \"write the draft\" — but how to translate a logical flow into actual sentences, how to hit exactly 4-6 sentences, when to use which transition word, how to land the pivot sentence — none of that is encoded anywhere.\n\nThat's exactly why the draft came out wrong. Missing H3 structure, missing H2 intros, wrong use of \"perhaps,\" Chinese characters leaking in. The canvas was perfect. The prose execution failed.\n\nSo the real question is: what does a drafting skill need to contain? Because the outlining methodology is documented now. The drafting execution is not.\n\nWant me to build that next?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":74128,"output":448,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775899412876}}
