{"type":"message","id":"a7fb622f","parentId":"93db3f38","timestamp":"2026-04-11T09:31:49.864Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_20c85b13-e087-4d52-b4ad-49f5044479a4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":82519,"output":55,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82574,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775899909863}}
{"type":"message","id":"86939d22","parentId":"a7fb622f","timestamp":"2026-04-11T09:31:49.883Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_20c85b13-e087-4d52-b4ad-49f5044479a4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\n## Context Monitor — Tin's Rules (2026-03-20, updated 2026-03-24)\n\n### Morning Brief Protocol (2026-03-21) — MANDATORY\n- Flush screenshot folder (~/OpenClawScreenshots/) during morning brief\n\nWhen tasked with a morning brief:\n1. **Read session files from the last TWO days** from `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/` — use `read` tool on the JSONL files, NOT memory_search\n2. **Read today's memory file** (if exists)\n3. **Verify live data** — don't trust stale search results (check ESPN/Premier League directly for fixtures)\n4. **Compile brief** — then deliver\n\n**Session file naming pattern:** `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/{uuid}.jsonl`\n- Filter by date in filename or modified time\n\nIf session files are unavailable or unreadable, flag it explicitly — do not proceed with stale data.\n\n### Heartbeat intervals\n| Situation | Interval | Actions |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Active** — user input within last 2-3 heartbeats | 10 min | Save memory checkpoint |\n| **Inactive** — no user input for 2-3 heartbeats | 30 min | Nothing unless assigned |\n| **Assignment active** — working on a task for user | 10 min | Save memory checkpoint |\n| **Complex assignment** | 10 min | Save memory checkpoint (never 5 min — causes cascade) |\n| **User signs off** (says going to bed, or silent after 23:00 + 1h inactive) | — | Backup before sleeping |\n\n### Backups\n- Only on request OR before config changes OR when user signs off\n- `mkdir -p ~/TinyBackUp/$(date +%Y%m%d)` then copy relevant files\n\n### Active learning protocol (2026-03-20)\nTiny is teaching about NurseSphere / LTC process. Take notes in `memory/2026-03-20.md` as we go. This is for building the Nava agent — process knowledge is as important as content rules.\n\n### Before Any Task: Check Skills First (2026-03-22)\n- **ALWAYS read the relevant skill SKILL.md before using a tool or technique for the first time**\n- For session history: read `~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md` first, then use `jq` commands\n- For browser tasks: check TOOLS.md visible browser section first\n- For anything unfamiliar: check workspace skills folder before guessing\n- **This is a hard rule — not optional**\n\n### Resource Map Reminder (2026-03-23)\nWhen cold-starting on Nava tasks and asked to locate files, corpus content, or backups:\n- **Check MEMORY.md first** — it has a Workspace Resource Map section with all key paths\n- The map tells you where: nava-corpus/ (social), rag/clean_txt/ (blog articles), TinyBackUp/ (backups), docs/nava-content-system/ (Nava docs)\n- Also in the map: full installed skills table with locations and purposes\n- This prevents the assertion → wrong → admit cycle that happened on 2026-03-23\n- **Skills reminder**: If asked to use a skill, check the skills table in MEMORY.md for location + usage notes before proceeding\n\n### Transcript Bank (2026-03-25)\n- File: `memory/TrnsBank.md`\n- **Append every turn** after sending response — your message + Tiny's reply\n- Format: `## [timestamp] You:\\n{message}\\n\\n## [timestamp] Me:\\n{response}`\n- **Hard cap: 200 messages** — if TrnsBank reaches 200 messages, trigger analysis immediately (don't wait for sprint check-in)\n- Lock bank during analysis — Tiny signals ready, then I read/analyse/wipe\n- Never touch JSONL files\n\n### Sprint Check-in Protocol\n- Run every 2h during active work (cron: Context monitor (2h sprint check-in))\n- During check-in: update today's memory file with current project status\n- Do NOT include self-referential triggering language in the system event text\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775899909876}}
{"type":"message","id":"d66ea07d","parentId":"86939d22","timestamp":"2026-04-11T09:32:07.765Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_42461d94-9fa3-414b-a6b9-4300b411e3c1","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"## NC Article Status Update (11:31 UTC)\n\n**Today:**\n- AWAA Phase 4 delivered (Apr 11 morning session): full canvas, H2.1-H2.4, all H3s, callouts, FAQ, bottom line\n- Tiny confirmed Phase 4 canvas was never formally approved — workflow violation\n- Phase 4 approved by Tiny via explicit instruction\n- Phase 5 spawned without approval → Tiny deleted draft immediately\n- Message loop crisis: `@d` marker confused routing, caused 10+ message loop\n- Marker system established: `@t` (me→Tiny), `@d` (Tiny→me), `@aw` (AWAA→me)\n- AWAA system prompt updated: file output only + `@aw` marker\n- Phase 4 fixes: Chinese characters (2x), wrong hedge context, meta-commentary removed\n- Canvas passes editor review after 4 fixes\n- Phase 5 re-spawned after Tiny approved canvas, draft generated\n- Editor review: draft missing H3 structure, missing H2.1 intro, continuous prose\n- Tiny confirmed: canvas is the gold standard, not the draft\n- `phased-outlining` skill created (workspace skills) — stops at Phase 4\n- Phase 5 (prose drafting) not in skill — drafting skill gap identified\n- Tiny: \"You have no fucking clue how to draft yet\"\n\n**NC article draft:** In `abroadworks/article-independent-contractor-non-compete.md`. Awaiting rewrite from canvas.","old_string":"## NC Article Status Update (11:31 UTC)","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-11.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":83620,"output":615,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84235,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775899927765}}
