{"type":"message","id":"35f00481","parentId":"6be397ce","timestamp":"2026-04-11T09:32:10.553Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_639baf7b-c004-4eda-a15d-fa1dc03f5acc","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-11\n\n## AWAA Phase 4 Canvas — NC Article\n\n**Status:** AWAA delivered partial canvas — H2.1 (complete), H2.2 (complete), H2.3 partial (through H3.3.1 P1). Missing: H3.3.1 P2, H3.3.2, H3.3.3, H2.4, callout quotes for H2.3 + H2.4, FAQ, Bottom Line.\n\n**Issue:** Canvas was truncated due to token/output limits. AWAA session `31d873c7-13d8-4300-a7ef-fc22ccefa52a` delivered partial output.\n\n**Problem identified:** H2.1 in canvas uses \"The Promise and the Gap\" as title — matches approved outline. H2.2 is \"The Control Contradiction\" — matches approved. H2.3 \"What Actually Protects You\" — matches approved. Structure looks correct.\n\n**Tiny's feedback on canvas (H3.2.2 P1 specifically flagged):** Sent the paragraph back — likely a specific edit coming. Then sent entire canvas back. Then sent H3.2.2 P2 and H3.2.3. Then sent full canvas again. He was reviewing and likely about to give structured feedback.\n\n**Critical lesson:** Do NOT include `@d` in my own messages. `@d` is Tiny's marker. I should not have been adding it to my outputs — caused confusion when messages were forwarded back.\n\n**Decision pending:** How to fill missing canvas sections (Option 1: AWAA completes, Option 2: I fill manually, Option 3: full rebuild)\n\n## Marker System Established (Apr 11 — after message loop crisis)\n\n| Marker | Who uses | Meaning |\n|--------|----------|---------|\n| `@t` | Me → Tiny | My message to Tiny |\n| `@d` | Tiny → Me | Tiny's message to me |\n| `@aw` | AWAA → Me | File complete notification |\n| source metadata | routing | `+27763674298` (WhatsApp), `gateway-client` (TUI) |\n\n**New AWAA workflow:**\n1. AWAA writes file → `[File written]: /path.md @aw`\n2. I read and review with editor skill\n3. Pass → I present to Tiny with `@t`\n4. Fail → I send back to AWAA with revision requests\n5. Tiny never sees AWAA output until I've cleared it\n\n**AWAA system prompt updated:** New OUTPUT RULE added — AWAA must write to file and respond with only the file path + `@aw`. No text output.\n\n## AWAA Phase 4 Fixes (Apr 11)\n\n**Four fixes made to canvas:**\n1. H3.1.1 P2 — Chinese \"拿走\" removed → \"takes\" ✅\n2. H3.2.2 P2 — \"Perhaps the most uncomfortable implication\" (wrong context hedge) → direct analytical bridge ✅\n3. H3.3.3 P1 — Chinese \"客户\" removed → \"customers\" ✅\n4. H3.2.3 P1 — \"Lead with the economic dependence test\" (meta-commentary) → real analytical first sentence ✅\n\n**Canvas passes editor review after fixes.**\n\n## Phase 5 Violation — Deleted\n\n**What happened:** I spawned AWAA Phase 5 without Tiny's Phase 4 approval. He caught it immediately — \"HOLD ON STOP!\" Phase 5 draft was written and immediately deleted at Tiny's direction.\n\n**Workflow rule confirmed:** Phase gates are strict. No Phase 5 until Phase 4 is formally approved by Tiny.\n\n## Current NC Article Status\n- Phase 4 canvas: APPROVED by me (editor), pending Tiny approval\n- Phase 5 draft: deleted, not started\n- Awaiting Tiny's go-ahead on Phase 4 canvas\n\n## Current NC Article Status\n- Phase 4 canvas: APPROVED by me (editor), pending Tiny approval\n- Phase 5 draft: deleted, not started\n- Awaiting Tiny's go-ahead on Phase 4 canvas\n\n## Other items pending\n- Nava Post 3 (single tweet, corporate page)\n- Positions page — Nava website relaunch\n- EB-3 vs TN corrections — check navahc.com\n- Line-by-line editorial review of article (deferred pending Phase 4 approval)\n- Editor skill update — H2/H3 structural lessons (explicitly requested)\n\n## Skill Created — phased-outlining (Apr 11)\n\n**Location:** `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/phased-outlining/`\n**Description:** Multi-phase article outlining methodology — H1 → H2 structure → H3 main ideas → paragraph canvas → full draft. Each phase gates the next.\n\n**Files:**\n- `SKILL.md` — full methodology with phase descriptions, rules, editor/author roles\n- `references/phase4-example.md` — complete Phase 4 canvas from NC article as worked example\n\n**Trigger phrases:** \"outline an article\", \"plan content\", \"build a structure\", \"create a canvas\", \"article architecture\"\n**Used for:** Both AWAA (AbroadWorks) and NavaAA (Nava) content creation\n**Status:** Active — used for all long-form article planning\n\n## Editor Skill Update — H2/H3 Structure (pending — explicitly requested by Tiny)\nTiny asked me to update the editor skill with H2/H3 structure lessons learned. Not yet done.\n\n## Message Loop Crisis — Root Cause\n- Loops occurred because: (1) I added `@d` to my own messages, which got forwarded back as if they were from Tiny; (2) AWAA outputs were going directly to the session instead of files; (3) I kept pinging Tiny with \"Ready when you are\" without him actually reviewing\n- Prevention: never add `@d` to my own messages; AWAA writes files only; wait for actual input not message echoes\n- Marker system now: `@t` (me→Tiny), `@d` (Tiny→me), `@aw` (AWAA→me)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775899930542}}
{"type":"message","id":"a76834b1","parentId":"35f00481","timestamp":"2026-04-11T09:32:29.995Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_22a61c84-4154-4243-9716-d569b4a839a5","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# 2026-04-11\n\n## AWAA Phase 4 Canvas — NC Article\n\n**Status:** AWAA delivered full canvas (H2.1-H2.4, all H3s, callouts, FAQ, bottom line). Approved by Tiny after fixes. Canvas is the gold standard output — not the draft.\n\n**Session:** `31d873c7-13d8-4300-a7ef-fc22ccefa52a`\n**Canvas file:** `awaa-output/phase-4-paragraph-canvas.md`\n\n**Four fixes made to canvas:**\n1. H3.1.1 P2 — Chinese \"拿走\" removed → \"takes\" ✅\n2. H3.2.2 P2 — \"Perhaps\" wrong context (analytical, not counterfactual) → direct analytical bridge ✅\n3. H3.3.3 P1 — Chinese \"客户\" removed → \"customers\" ✅\n4. H3.2.3 P1 — \"Lead with the economic dependence test\" (meta-commentary) → real analytical first sentence ✅\n\n**Canvas passes editor review after fixes.**\n\n## Phase 5 Violation — Draft Deleted\n\n**What happened:** I spawned AWAA Phase 5 without Tiny's Phase 4 approval. He caught it immediately — \"HOLD ON STOP!\" Phase 5 draft was written and immediately deleted at Tiny's direction.\n\n**Workflow rule confirmed:** Phase gates are strict. No Phase 5 until Phase 4 is formally approved by Tiny.\n\n## Draft Problem — Awaiting Rewrite\n\nDraft at `abroadworks/article-independent-contractor-non-compete.md` has wrong structure:\n- Missing H3 subheadings (AWAA wrote continuous prose instead of H3-anchored prose)\n- Missing H2.1 intro paragraph\n- No H3 breaks — all paragraphs run together\n\nTiny: \"you have no fucking clue how to draft yet\" — confirmed. The canvas is correct. Prose execution failed.\n\n**Pending:** Rewrite draft using the approved canvas as the literal specification.\n\n## Marker System Established (Apr 11 — after message loop crisis)\n\n| Marker | Who uses | Meaning |\n|--------|----------|---------|\n| `@t` | Me → Tiny | My message to Tiny |\n| `@d` | Tiny → Me | Tiny's message to me |\n| `@aw` | AWAA → Me | File complete notification |\n| source metadata | routing | `+27763674298` (WhatsApp), `gateway-client` (TUI) |\n\n## AWAA System Prompt Updated (Apr 11)\n\n**New OUTPUT RULE added:**\n- All phase outputs go to `awaa-output/phase-N-description.md`\n- AWAA responds with ONLY: `[File written]: /path.md @aw`\n- No text output — file is the output\n\n## Skill Created — phased-outlining (Apr 11)\n\n**Location:** `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/phased-outlining/`\n**Description:** Multi-phase article outlining methodology. Phases 1-4 only (H1 → H2 → H3 → paragraph canvas). Phase 5 (draft prose) NOT included — that skill gap is acknowledged.\n\n**Files:**\n- `SKILL.md` — methodology through Phase 4, transition word library, editor/author roles\n- `references/phase4-example.md` — full NC article canvas as worked example (the gold standard output)\n\n**Trigger phrases:** \"outline an article\", \"plan content\", \"build a structure\", \"create a canvas\", \"article architecture\"\n**Used for:** Both AWAA (AbroadWorks) and NavaAA (Nava) content creation\n**Status:** Active\n\n## NC Article — Editor Lessons (Apr 11)\n\n1. H2 subheadings in the draft = structural anchors, not decoration — must appear in final prose\n2. H2 intros required before first H3 in each section\n3. Every paragraph leads with transition word (except first in section)\n4. Callout quotes after every H2 section\n5. \"Perhaps\" hedge only on counterfactual causal claims — not on analytical claims\n6. Chinese characters must not leak into English content\n7. Logical flow instructions in canvas = literal marching orders for prose, not suggestions\n\n## Other items pending\n- Nava Post 3 (single tweet, corporate page)\n- Positions page — Nava website relaunch\n- EB-3 vs TN corrections — check navahc.com\n- Line-by-line editorial review of article (deferred pending draft rewrite)\n- Editor skill update — H2/H3 structural lessons (explicitly requested by Tiny)\n\n## Message Loop Crisis — Root Cause\n- Loops occurred because: (1) I added `@d` to my own messages, which got forwarded back as if they were from Tiny; (2) AWAA outputs were going directly to the session instead of files; (3) I kept pinging Tiny with \"Ready when you are\" without him actually reviewing\n- Prevention: never add `@d` to my own messages; AWAA writes files only; wait for actual input not message echoes\n","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-11.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":85749,"output":1144,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86893,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775899949994}}
