{"type":"compaction","id":"8347a191","parentId":"d284342e","timestamp":"2026-04-11T09:34:46.539Z","summary":"## Decisions\n- **Option B confirmed by Tiny**: Proceed directly to draft evaluation, skip separate Phase 4 canvas review gate\n- **Phase gate breach acknowledged**: AWAA jumped straight to Phase 5 without waiting for Phase 4 approval — system prompt fix needed\n- **Line-by-line review initiated**: Assistant presented draft and asked Tiny for first change feedback\n- **Opening story preserved**: Provided story about developer using non-compete as leverage to work directly with clients must not be changed\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Line-by-line editorial review in progress — awaiting Tiny's first change feedback\n- Fix AWAA system prompt to enforce Phase 4 gate (AWAA must not spawn Phase 5 without explicit approval)\n- Editor skill update — H2/H3 structural lessons (explicitly requested by Tiny, not yet done)\n- Nava Post 3 — single tweet, corporate page (pending)\n- Positions page — Nava website relaunch (pending)\n- EB-3 vs TN corrections — check navahc.com (pending)\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- AWAA Phase workflow is strict: outline → H2 structure → H3 ideas → paragraph canvas → draft\n- Phase gates must be respected — each phase requires Tiny approval before next begins\n- 4–6 sentences per paragraph\n- Every paragraph (except first in section) must lead with a transition word\n- H2 intros required before each H2 section\n- Callout quotes required after each H2 section\n- FAQ: 3 questions with unique operational anxieties, no recycled math\n- No em-dashes, no contractions, no bold in body text\n- Primary keyword \"independent contractor non-compete\" must appear in H1, first paragraph, at least one H2, FAQ, and conclusion\n- Opening story (provided) must not be changed\n- \"Perhaps\" hedge ONLY on counterfactual causal claims, NOT analytical claims\n- No Chinese characters in English article content\n\n## Pending user asks\n- **Tiny is waiting for line-by-line review to begin** — assistant asked \"Line-by-line review starts whenever you're ready. Hit me with the first change.\"\n- No other pending requests\n\n## Exact identifiers\n\n**File paths:**\n- Draft: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/temp_awaa_nc_article.md`\n- Memory: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-11.md`\n- Article (pending move): `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/abroadworks/article-independent-contractor-non-compete.md`\n- AWAA system prompt: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/abroadworks-writing/awaa-system-prompt.md`\n- Editorial notes: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/NC-article-editorial-notes.md`\n\n**Session IDs:**\n- AWAA Phase 4 session: `agent:main:subagent:39673e80-5803-4bd7-b6a1-718581231b25`\n- AWAA Phase 5 session: `agent:main:subagent:23f57358-3d2d-45bd-9cde-8d5c7076ee37`\n- Phase 4 fixes subagent: `agent:main:subagent:c8599094-d103-462a-af26-81be9a69776c`\n\n**Message IDs:**\n- Phase 4 approval: `3EB0C3C3062FDCC6246F94`\n- Phase 5 go-ahead: `3EB0E583C26BF2C3B84A15`\n- Draft presented: `3EB072187331679F6936CC`\n- Option B confirmation: `3EB0CF5DC695608F68EB9A`\n- Review initiation: `3EB0B4687B51D9DF0BA857`\n\n**Sender:** `+27763674298`\n\n**Case cited:** Chavez-DeRemer (2024) — $9 million impact\n\n**States with non-compete bans:** California, Minnesota, North Dakota, Oklahoma, Washington State, District of Columbia\n\n**Article title:** Independent Contractor Non-Compete: What It Actually Covers (and What It Doesn't)\n\n**Guardrail commits:** `fdd0439`, `bd070a5`\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- User wants a standardized \"outlining skill\" created to document their process for multiple projects\n- Process is reusable across AW, Nava, and future NavaAA projects\n- Should use \"phase 4 output document\" as the example/template\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Create/document the outlining skill based on user's process\n- The assistant began reading the skill-creator SKILL.md for guidance\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- The process must work across multiple clients (not just AW)\n- Documentation should follow the skill-creator skill format\n- Use existing \"phase 4 output document\" as example reference\n\n## Pending user asks\n- User asked for the process to be documented as an \"outlining skill\"\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- Sender metadata ID: `gateway-client`\n- Sender metadata label: `openclaw-tui (gateway-client)`\n- Sender metadata name: `openclaw-tui`\n- Sender metadata username: `openclaw-tui`\n- Skill creator path: `/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md`\n- Skill name: `skill-creator`\n- Client projects mentioned: AW, Nava, NavaAA\n- Document reference: \"phase 4 output document\"\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-04-11 11:10 GMT+2] And this file so called finalised file, it follows the plan that was created in phase 4 with the multiple H3s?\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): 7:## The Promise and the Gap\n25:## The Control Contradiction\n43:## What Actually Protects You\n61:## When It Might Be Worth Using\n77:## Frequently Asked Questions\n79:### Can I enforce a non-compete if my contractor lives in a different state?\n83:### My contractor signed a non-compete but I never had them sign an IP assignment. What do I actually own?\n87:### What should I look for in a contractor agreement to avoid the problems described in this article?\n- Assistant: No. The draft is missing H3 structure.\n\nHere's the actual breakdown:\n\n**What canvas specified:**\n- H2.1 — 3 H3s (1.1.1, 1.1.2, 1.1.3), 6 paragraphs total\n- H2.2 — 3 H3s (2.2.1, 2.2.2, 2.2.3), 6 paragraphs total\n- H2.3 — 3 H3s (3.3.1, 3.3.2, 3.3.3), 6 paragraphs total\n- H2.4 — 2 H3s (4.4.1, 4.4.2), 4 paragraphs total\n\n**What the draft actually has:**\n- H2.1 — 2 paragraphs (H3.1.1 merged with H3.1.3, H3.1.2 missing entirely)\n- H2.2 — 5 paragraphs (but no H3 breaks, just continuous prose)\n- H2.3 — 5 paragraphs (same)\n- H2.4 — 4 paragraphs (same)\n\nThe H3s were supposed to be structural anchors in ...\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-04-11 11:12 GMT+2] Listen you stupid computer. There are several things you are failing to understand here. We painstakingly built the phase 4 annotate outine with paragraph ideas and logical flow, correct?\n- Assistant: Yes. Correct.\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-04-11 11:13 GMT+2] The process up to this point is the gold standard. I think we should document it somewhere and make sure this process is never forgotten.\n- Assistant: Agreed. This process — H1 approval, H2 structure, H3 main ideas with logical flows, paragraph canvas with transitions, then draft — is the actual IP here. Not the article, the methodology.\n\nI should document it in `skills/abroadworks-writing/` as a permanent SOP. Should take about 5 minutes.\n\nWant me to do that now while the draft is being finalized?\n\n<read-files>\n/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-4-paragraph-canvas.md\n\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-5-full-draft.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-11.md\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/abroadworks-writing/awaa-system-prompt.md\n\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"4e71c558","tokensBefore":87222,"details