{"type":"message","id":"d83bd0e3","parentId":"8347a191","timestamp":"2026-04-11T09:34:46.730Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-04-11 11:31 GMT+2] No, here is how you execute phase 5. \n1. You tell AWAA to simply now convert the paragraph ideas and logical flows into actual paragraphs! Don't touch the headings, don't touch the intros, don't touch the conclusion, or the FAQs. Your only job is to convert the paragraph ideas+logical flows into full paragraphs.\n2. Once the full paragraphs are in place, revise the H2 intros to make sure they represent what's discussed in the sections.\n3. Check for transitions between paragraphs. You will need to help here because you have the transitions skill - the one that's about connecting ideas, not just adding transition words.\n4. Finally, check the FAQs and to ensure they reflect the article.\n\nWe will call this your drafting-skill - the ability to convert the gold standard phase 4 annotated outline into a full article."}],"timestamp":1775900086722}}
