{"type":"message","id":"804acd71","parentId":"c3cfc0f2","timestamp":"2026-04-11T09:42:34.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNot yet. Spawning it now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_dfe86376-6feb-4018-8728-990ee7ba9866","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"mode":"run","runtime":"subagent","task":"## Task: Phase 5 — Draft from Canvas\n\nRead the Phase 4 canvas at `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-4-paragraph-canvas.md` and the drafting skill at `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/drafting-skill/SKILL.md`.\n\nExecute Phase 5 using the 4-step method:\n\n**Step 1 — Convert paragraph ideas to full prose:**\n- For each H3 section, write the two paragraphs following the canvas logical flow sentence-by-sentence\n- Do NOT touch the headings, H2 intros, FAQ, or bottom line — only write the body paragraphs\n- 4-6 sentences per paragraph\n- Every paragraph (except first in a section) opens with a transition word\n- No em-dashes, no contractions\n- \"Perhaps\" only on counterfactual causal claims\n\n**Step 2 — Revise H2 intros:**\n- Check that each H2 intro paragraph accurately represents what the section covers\n- Revise if needed\n\n**Step 3 — Check transitions:**\n- Use transitions-skill at `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/transitions-skill/SKILL.md` to audit paragraph transitions\n- Fix any broken vocabulary bridges or logical threads\n\n**Step 4 — Check FAQs:**\n- Verify each FAQ question is derivable from the article's actual argument\n- Revise questions if they don't match\n\n**Output:** Write the complete draft to `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-5-full-draft.md`\n\n**Response format:** Only — `[File written]: /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-5-full-draft.md @aw`\n\nDo not write full text in chat. File is the output."}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":54292,"output":746