{"type":"compaction","id":"25c2d55f","parentId":"807025ef","timestamp":"2026-04-11T10:45:36.098Z","summary":"## Decisions\n- **Option B confirmed by Tiny**: Proceed directly to draft evaluation, skip separate Phase 4 canvas review gate\n- **Phase gate breach acknowledged**: AWAA jumped straight to Phase 5 without waiting for Phase 4 approval — system prompt fix needed\n- **Line-by-line review initiated**: Assistant presented draft and asked Tiny for first change feedback\n- **Opening story preserved**: Provided story about developer using non-compete as leverage to work directly with clients must not be changed\n- **Skills documented and committed**: `drafting-skill` and `transitions-skill` created and pushed to git\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Line-by-line editorial review in progress — awaiting Tiny's first change feedback\n- Fix AWAA system prompt to enforce Phase 4 gate (AWAA must not spawn Phase 5 without explicit approval)\n- Editor skill update — H2/H3 structural lessons (explicitly requested by Tiny, not yet done)\n- Nava Post 3 — single tweet, corporate page (pending)\n- Positions page — Nava website relaunch (pending)\n- EB-3 vs TN corrections — check navahc.com (pending)\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- AWAA Phase workflow is strict: outline → H2 structure → H3 ideas → paragraph canvas → draft\n- Phase gates must be respected — each phase requires Tiny approval before next begins\n- 4–6 sentences per paragraph\n- Every paragraph (except first in section) must lead with a transition word\n- H2 intros required before each H2 section\n- Callout quotes required after each H2 section\n- FAQ: 3 questions with unique operational anxieties, no recycled math\n- No em-dashes, no contractions, no bold in body text\n- Primary keyword \"independent contractor non-compete\" must appear in H1, first paragraph, at least one H2, FAQ, and conclusion\n- Opening story (provided) must not be changed\n- \"Perhaps\" hedge ONLY on counterfactual causal claims, NOT analytical claims\n- No Chinese characters in English article content\n- Canvas logical flow = literal marching orders for prose, not suggestions\n\n## Pending user asks\n- **Tiny is waiting for line-by-line review to begin** — assistant asked \"Line-by-line review starts whenever you're ready. Hit me with the first change.\"\n- No other pending requests\n\n## Exact identifiers\n\n**File paths:**\n- Draft: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/temp_awaa_nc_article.md`\n- Memory: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-11.md`\n- Article (pending move): `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/abroadworks/article-independent-contractor-non-compete.md`\n- AWAA system prompt: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/abroadworks-writing/awaa-system-prompt.md`\n- Editorial notes: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/NC-article-editorial-notes.md`\n- Phase 4 canvas: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-4-paragraph-canvas.md`\n- Phase 5 draft: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-5-full-draft.md`\n\n**Skills created (committed):**\n- `drafting-skill`: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/drafting-skill/SKILL.md`\n- `transitions-skill`: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/work\n\n[Compaction summary truncated to fit budget]\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Goal\nClean up and finalize the Markdown draft article about contractor non-compete clauses by fixing two categories of issues: (1) a Chinese character leak that appeared in the prose, and (2) missing transition words at the start of non-first paragraphs within H3 sections.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Every paragraph within an H3 section (except the first paragraph of that section) must open with a transition word from the approved set (Furthermore, Moreover, In addition, Yet, Nevertheless, Still, Despite this, Consequently, Therefore, As a result, Worse, Beyond, Even more, For instance, Consider, Take the case of, Although, Even if, Granted)\n- Paragraphs are separated by blank lines (blank-line-delimited structure)\n- Chinese characters must not appear in the final document\n- Edits must match text exactly including all whitespace\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Found Chinese character \"带走\" at line 77; replaced with \"take with them on a laptop.\"\n- [x] Fixed line 47: \"When you send...\" → \"Consequently, when you send...\"\n- [x] Fixed line 79: \"The key to trade secret protection...\" → \"Furthermore, the key to trade secret protection...\"\n- [x] Fixed line 85: \"The non-solicitation clause works...\" → \"Furthermore, the non-solicitation clause works...\"\n- [x] Fixed line 99: \"The honest assessment...\" → \"Consequently, the honest assessment...\"\n- [x] Fixed line 105: \"Ask the second question directly...\" → \"Therefore, ask the second question directly...\"\n- [x] Fixed H3.2.2 second paragraph: Added \"Consequently, the lesson is not that you should avoid non-competes entirely.\"\n- [x] Fixed H3.2.3 second paragraph: \"This creates a structural bind.\" → \"Nevertheless, this creates a structural bind.\"\n- [x] Ran final Chinese character sweep via `grep -n -E '[^\\x00-\\x7F]'`; results truncated before confirmation\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Awaiting confirmation that the Chinese character sweep returned zero true positives (the grep output was truncated mid-display; matched lines include markdown syntax characters — further inspection needed to verify no Chinese characters remain)\n- [ ] FAQ section was reviewed and declared solid; no fixes applied there\n\n### Blocked\n- The grep `[^\\x00-\\x7F]` sweep output was truncated at 23729+ characters, making it impossible to confirm whether any actual non-ASCII characters remain. The match lines shown include markdown formatting (`#`, `**`) which are ASCII — false positives from the regex. A targeted sweep for CJK Unicode ranges would give a cleaner result.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Use \"Consequently\" for enforcement/misclassification paragraphs**: Signals direct causal chain (enforc