{"type":"compaction","id":"3b7dad73","parentId":"54108f39","timestamp":"2026-04-11T10:59:20.921Z","summary":"## Decisions\n- **Option B confirmed by Tiny**: Proceed directly to draft evaluation, skip separate Phase 4 canvas review gate\n- **Phase gate breach acknowledged**: AWAA jumped straight to Phase 5 without waiting for Phase 4 approval — system prompt fix needed\n- **Line-by-line review initiated**: Assistant presented draft and asked Tiny for first change feedback\n- **Opening story preserved**: Provided story about developer using non-compete as leverage to work directly with clients must not be changed\n- **Skills documented and committed**: `drafting-skill` and `transitions-skill` created and pushed to git\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Line-by-line editorial review in progress — awaiting Tiny's first change feedback\n- Fix AWAA system prompt to enforce Phase 4 gate (AWAA must not spawn Phase 5 without explicit approval)\n- Editor skill update — H2/H3 structural lessons (explicitly requested by Tiny, not yet done)\n- Nava Post 3 — single tweet, corporate page (pending)\n- Positions page — Nava website relaunch (pending)\n- EB-3 vs TN corrections — check navahc.com (pending)\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- AWAA Phase workflow is strict: outline → H2 structure → H3 ideas → paragraph canvas → draft\n- Phase gates must be respected — each phase requires Tiny approval before next begins\n- 4–6 sentences per paragraph\n- Every paragraph (except first in section) must lead with a transition word\n- H2 intros required before each H2 section\n- Callout quotes required after each H2 section\n- FAQ: 3 questions with unique operational anxieties, no recycled math\n- No em-dashes, no contractions, no bold in body text\n- Primary keyword \"independent contractor non-compete\" must appear in H1, first paragraph, at least one H2, FAQ, and conclusion\n- Opening story (provided) must not be changed\n- \"Perhaps\" hedge ONLY on counterfactual causal claims, NOT analytical claims\n- No Chine