s (blank-line-delimited structure)\n- Chinese characters must not appear in the final document\n- Edits must match text exactly including all whitespace\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Found Chinese character \"带走\" at line 77; replaced with \"take with them on a laptop.\"\n- [x] Fixed line 47: \"When you send...\" → \"Consequently, when you send...\"\n- [x] Fixed line 79: \"The key to trade secret protection...\" → \"Furthermore, the key to trade secret protection...\"\n- [x] Fixed line 85: \"The non-solicitation clause works...\" → \"Furthermore, the non-solicitation clause works...\"\n- [x] Fixed line 99: \"The honest assessment...\" → \"Consequently, the honest assessment...\"\n- [x] Fixed line 105: \"Ask the second question directly...\" → \"Therefore, ask the second question directly...\"\n- [x] Fixed H3.2.2 second paragraph: Added \"Consequently, the lesson is not that you should avoid non-competes entirely.\"\n- [x] Fixed H3.2.3 second paragraph: \"This creates a structural bind.\" → \"Nevertheless, this creates a structural bind.\"\n- [x] Ran final Chinese character sweep via `grep -n -E '[^\\x00-\\x7F]'`; results truncated before confirmation\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Awaiting confirmation that the Chinese character sweep returned zero true positives (the grep output was truncated mid-display; matched lines include markdown syntax characters — further inspection needed to verify no Chinese characters remain)\n- [ ] FAQ section was reviewed and declared solid; no fixes applied there\n\n### Blocked\n- The grep `[^\\x00-\\x7F]` sweep output was truncated at 23729+ characters, making it impossible to confirm whether any actual non-ASCII characters remain. The match lines shown include markdown formatting (`#`, `**`) which are ASCII — false positives from the regex. A targeted sweep for CJK Unicode ranges would give a cleaner result.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Use \"Consequently\" for enforcement/misclassification paragraphs**: Signals direct causal chain (enforce non-compete → demonstrates control → triggers misclassification).\n- **Use \"Furthermore\" for additive/positive paragraphs**: Trade secret protection and non-solicitation are additive tools, not reactive consequences.\n- **Use \"Nevertheless\" for the structural bind paragraph**: Contradicts the expectation that non-competes provide protection.\n- **Use \"Therefore\" for the question-asking paragraph**: Leads to a recommended action from the preceding diagnostic.\n- **Script abandoned**: The blank-line paragraph-boundary logic in the Python script was incorrect; switched to manual read/edit passes per paragraph.\n\n## Decisions\n- Fixed Chinese character leak by replacing \"带走\" with \"take with them on a laptop\" at line 77.\n- Added transition words (\"Consequently\", \"Furthermore\", \"Nevertheless\", \"Therefore\") to 8 paragraphs across H3.2.2, H3.2.3, H3.3.2, H3.3.3, H3.4.2, and H3.5.2.\n- All transitions target the approved transition word set; no unapproved words used.\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Confirm no Chinese/non-ASCII characters remain in the document. The final `grep -E '[^\\x00-\\x7F]'` sweep was cut off before its conclusion. A targeted sweep (e.g., `grep -n -E '[\\x{4E00}-\\x{9FFF}]'` for CJK characters, or re-running the full grep and inspecting the tail) should be executed to verify.\n- The conversation ends mid-sweep; no explicit \"done\" confirmation was given by the assistant before the session was cut.\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Paragraph transition rule: Every paragraph in an H3 section (except the first) must begin with a transition word from: Furthermore, Moreover, In addition, Yet, Nevertheless, Still, Despite this, Consequently, Therefore, As a result, Worse, Beyond, Even more, For instance, Consider, Take the case of, Although, Even if, Granted.\n- Edit tool requires exact string match including whitespace and newlines.\n- File: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-5-full-draft.md`\n- Section structure: H2 sections at lines 13, 39, 65, 91, 111, 127; H3 sections as listed in audit output.\n\n## Pending user asks\n- No explicit pending user ask. The original user message was a system echo of WhatsApp gateway disconnections followed by an assistant draft review noting the Chinese character leak and transition gaps. The assistant self-assigned the fixes.\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- File path: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-5-full-draft.md`\n- Message ID: `3EB0F36FC688ECD7A4834B`\n- Sender ID: `+27763674298`\n- Chinese character found: `带走` (line 77, replaced with `take with them on a laptop`)\n- Section headers (exact):\n  - Line 13: `## The Promise and the Gap`\n  - Line 17: `### What the Clause Actually Restricts`\n  - Line 23: `### The Enforceability Landscape`\n  - Line 29: `### Why the Geographic Patchwork Makes the Protection Feel Absolute When It Is Not`\n  - Line 39: `## The Control Contradiction`\n  - Line 43: `### The Mechanism: Enforcement Becomes the Evidence of Misclassification`\n  - Line 49: `### The Chavez-DeRemer Case: $9 Million Judgment Where the Non-Compete Was the Exhibit, Not the Primary Liability`\n  - Line 55: `### The Irony: The More You Try to Protect, the More You Demonstrate Economic Dependence`\n  - Line 65: `## What Actually Protects You`\n  - Line 69: `### IP Assignment: The Foundation Most Agreements Skip`\n  - Line 75: `### Trade Secret Law: Federal, State-Robust, Covers the Information Problem`\n  - Line 81: `### Non-Solicitation: The Clause That Actually Targets Client Relationships`\n  - Line 91: `## When It Might Be Worth Using`\n  - Line 95: `### The Narrow Scenario Where It Holds (Threshold Met + Genuine Independence + Narrow Scope)`\n  - Line 101: `### The Real Question to Ask Your Provider`\n  - Line 111: `## Frequently Asked Questions`\n  - Line 127: `## Bottom Line`\n- Approved transition words: `Furthermore`, `Moreover`, `In addition`, `Yet`, `Nevertheless`, `Still`, `Despite this`, `Consequently`, `Therefore`, `As a resu