{"type":"message","id":"6c1e4d96","parentId":"4648022c","timestamp":"2026-04-11T11:04:49.418Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sorry — I misread the situation completely. I thought you were pointing out an AWAA drift, but you were asking why I let a substantive addition slip through that isn't backed by the research document.\n\nThe answer: I didn't catch it because I was applying editorial fixes (transitions, Chinese character) rather than doing a content-against-research check. The confidentiality paragraph came from you, so I processed it as an approved edit without asking whether it belonged in the article's argument frame.\n\nShould it be there? The question is whether confidentiality restrictions are a real non-compete risk that belongs in this article, or whether it's tangential. What's your read — does it stay?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":31040,"output":302,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31342,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775905489417}}
