{"type":"message","id":"0d7bedaf","parentId":"78ec58b3","timestamp":"2026-04-11T11:27:01.537Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Noted. Two distinct passes:\n\n**Pass 1 — Arc & Structure:** Does the argument work? Does each section have a distinct job? Are we saying something that's actually true and specific, or are we skating on generic claims?\n\n**Pass 2 — Readability Sweep:** Does it sound like it was written by a person thinking, or does it have the texture of a template? Every phrase that could live in any article in the same category — gone. Every sentence that doesn't move the argument forward – cut.\n\nI'll run both on each section as you finish it, not after the whole thing. What's next?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":63279,"output":292,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63571,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775906821534}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d74c409","parentId":"0d7bedaf","timestamp":"2026-04-11T11:29:25.108Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-04-11 13:29 GMT+2] No, I mean you should be doing these passes when you get the final draft from AWAA. If these changes are editorial, then you make them (readability sweep). But if we have major issues (arc and structure), you need to send it back to AWAA with instructions. Does that make sense? This review I am doing is for you to take notes and understand the concepts or reasons why I am making certain changes."}],"timestamp":1775906965081}}
{"type":"message","id":"142e684f","parentId":"6d74c409","timestamp":"2026-04-11T11:29:41.355Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That makes complete sense. I was conflating three things:\n\n1. **AWAA output → me:** I do arc/structure check. If broken, send back to AWAA. If fine, I do a readability sweep and fix what I can.\n\n2. **Your line-by-line review → learning material:** Your changes are teaching me the editorial principles behind your judgment. I note them, absorb them, and apply them to future drafts — not retroactively to the current one.\n\n3. **Your edits vs. my edits:** You're making substantive editorial decisions. I'm tracking the *why* so I can internalize the pattern.\n\nSo the draft I have in front of me — I should run my readability pass on it now, not wait for your review. And your H3-by-H3 review is training data for my editorial instincts, not a revision log to replicate.\n\nRun the readability sweep on the current draft now. Correct the \"X is not just Y\" patterns, the thin transitions, anything that reads like a template. Then we have a clean draft ready for your line-by-line when you get to it.\n\nOn it."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":63571,"output":425,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63996,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775906981354}}
