{"type":"message","id":"ac22db28","parentId":"3bd95fcc","timestamp":"2026-04-11T12:05:53.052Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the comparison. Two different H2.2 intros and first H3s:\n\n**My original draft (`temp_awaa_nc_article.md`):**\n\nH2.2 intro — behavioral scene, no mechanism:\n> \"It may seem that structuring the working relationship carefully bridges the gap between what a non-compete promises and what it actually delivers. Owners often respond by increasing oversight. They specify work hours. They require the contractor to use company tools. They dictate the sequence of tasks. These steps feel protective. They create a legal problem instead.\"\n\nH3.3.1 (Mechanism) — the mechanism:\n> \"The more you control how, when, and where a contractor works, the more you look like an employer. Courts and state agencies look at the totality of the relationship, not the labels in the paperwork...\"\n\n---\n\n**AWAA's Phase 5 (pre-tiny-review.md):**\n\nH2.2 intro — announces mechanism, then explains it:\n> \"There is a second problem with non-competes that most articles do not mention, and it runs in the opposite direction from the first. The clause does not just fail to protect you. Used aggressively, it can actively create liability. The mechanism is counterintuitive and it works like this. Courts determine whether a worker is an independent contractor or an employee by examining the degree of control...\"\n\nH3.3.1 (Mechanism) — repeats the exact same courts/control paragraph:\n> \"Courts determine whether a worker is an employee or an independent contractor by looking at the degree of control the hiring business exercises...\"\n\n---\n\nThe structural failure: AWAA's intro does the H3's job, then H3.3.1 repeats it. My original had the intro do one job (establish the behavioral instinct that creates the problem) and H3.3.1 do its own job (explain the mechanism)."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":65215,"output":1333,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66548,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775909153049}}
