home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag_abroadworks/drafts/independent_contractor_non_compete_v7.md\n/ho...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): 9:Most micro-business owners want a non-compete for the same reason: they are trying to protect one of three things. The client relationships they spent years building. The proprietary knowledge embedded in their processes and systems. The competitive moat they constructed through deliberate work. A non-compete does none of these. It restricts where a contractor can work after the relationship ends — a geographic or market-based exclusion that activates only when the engagement is already over. The basic restriction is narrower than most owners assume, and that narrowness is the gap between wh...\n- Assistant: It does. Line 9 of the research lists \"proprietary knowledge embedded in their processes and systems\" as one of the three things owners try to protect. Lines 47-49 cover trade secret law and confidentiality clauses specifically — \"invoking\" trade secret protection by marking information as proprietary and including a confidentiality clause in the agreement.\n\nSo the confidentiality material is in the research. I misidentified it as AWAA drift when you added it — but you were right to add it because it's explicitly in the source. My mistake.\n\nThe distinction is real though: the research talks ab...\n- User: System: [2026-04-11 13:06:45 GMT+2] WhatsApp gateway disconnected (status 499)\nSystem: [2026-04-11 13:06:51 GMT+2] WhatsApp gateway connected.\nSystem: [2026-04-11 13:07:51 GMT+2] WhatsApp gateway disconnected (status 499)\nSystem: [2026-04-11 13:07:58 GMT+2] WhatsApp gateway connected.\nSystem: [2026-04-11 13:08:58 GMT+2] WhatsApp gateway disconnected (status 499)\nSystem: [2026-04-11 13:09:09 GMT+2] WhatsApp gateway connected.\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",