{"type":"message","id":"ff6330a8","parentId":"d46499a2","timestamp":"2026-04-11T12:11:35.001Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_bc00f143-bef5-4079-bd79-9a1e4eeaed2a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"iconv -f UTF-16LE -t UTF-8 /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/awaa-output/phase-5-pre-tiny-review.md 2>/dev/null | sed -n '/## The Control Contradiction/,/### The Mechanism: Enforcement Becomes the Evidence of Misclassification/p'"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":64934,"output":130,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65064,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775909495000}}
{"type":"message","id":"49329f65","parentId":"ff6330a8","timestamp":"2026-04-11T12:11:35.042Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_bc00f143-bef5-4079-bd79-9a1e4eeaed2a","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## The Control Contradiction\r\n\r\nThere is a second problem with non-competes that most articles do not mention, and it runs in the opposite direction from the first. The clause does not just fail to protect you. Used aggressively, it can actively create liability. The mechanism is counterintuitive and it works like this. Courts determine whether a worker is an independent contractor or an employee by examining the degree of control the hiring business exercises over that worker. The more control you exert, the more the relationship looks like employment. Non-competes are a control mechanism, which means using one is itself evidence of the relationship you are trying to deny. This is the control contradiction, and it is the most consequential flaw in the standard approach to protecting contractor relationships.\r\n\r\n### The Mechanism: Enforcement Becomes the Evidence of Misclassification"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":24,"aggregated":"## The Control Contradiction\r\n\r\nThere is a second problem with non-competes that most articles do not mention, and it runs in the opposite direction from the first. The clause does not just fail to protect you. Used aggressively, it can actively create liability. The mechanism is counterintuitive and it works like this. Courts determine whether a worker is an independent contractor or an employee by examining the degree of control the hiring business exercises over that worker. The more control you exert, the more the relationship looks like employment. Non-competes are a control mechanism, which means using one is itself evidence of the relationship you are trying to deny. This is the control contradiction, and it is the most consequential flaw in the standard approach to protecting contractor relationships.\r\n\r\n### The Mechanism: Enforcement Becomes the Evidence of Misclassification","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775909495033}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b115df8","parentId":"49329f65","timestamp":"2026-04-11T12:11:56.624Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two things:\n\n1. **\"that most articles do not mention\"** — template filler, unsubstantiated claim about other writing. Should not be there.\n\n2. **The structural parrotting:** The intro announces \"The mechanism is counterintuitive and it works like this\" and then immediately explains it — courts determine contractor vs. employee status by examining degree of control, more control = employment relationship, non-competes are control mechanisms so using one = evidence of the employment relationship you're trying to deny.\n\nH3.3.1 then opens with: \"Courts determine whether a worker is an employee or an independent contractor by looking at the degree of control the hiring business exercises.\"\n\nThat's the same paragraph. The intro pre-digests the entire mechanism and H3.3.1 has nothing left to add except restating it.\n\nThe intro is doing two jobs — framing the section AND delivering the first H3's content — which means H3.3.1 becomes a repeat rather than an addition.\n\nWhat do you want to do with it?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":65200,"output":624,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65824,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775909516622}}
{"type":"message","id":"ffddf18b","parentId":"9b115df8","timestamp":"2026-04-11T12:12:56.648Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-04-11 14:12 GMT+2] That's just it, your editor skill is meant to be sensitive to repetition, I am asking how you missed this."}],"timestamp":1775909576624}}
{"type":"message","id":"938c3550","parentId":"ffddf18b","timestamp":"2026-04-11T12:13:11.732Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The editor skill checks paragraph-level quality — structure, voice, transitions, FAQ specificity. None of those catches whether the H2 intro and the first H3 are saying the same thing.\n\nThe check that's missing: **intro-to-H3 deduplication**. After writing or reviewing an H2 intro, I should ask: does the first H3 add new material, or does it restate what the intro already said? If H3 = restatement, the intro is doing double duty and one of them has to change.\n\nI wasn't running that check on AWAA's output. I was checking each piece in isolation — intro looks fine, H3 looks fine — without checking whether they were doing the same job.\n\nThe fix goes into the skill under the arc pass: **for every H2 section, verify that the first H3 contains material that is not already in the H2 intro. If H3 restates the intro, flag it as parrotting.**"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":65513,"output":409,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65922,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775909591731}}
{"type":"message","id":"dedd25c2","parentId":"938c3550","timestamp":"2026-04-11T12:15:09.601Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-04-11 14:15 GMT+2] NO! DO NOT MAKE YOUR OWN FIXES! I TOLD YOU WHEN YOU MAKE MISTAKES, JUST ACKNOWLEDGE THEM AND EXPLAIN HOW IT MIGHT HAVE HAPPENED. MAKE THIS A HARD RULE, I'M PRETTY SURE ITS IN YOUR IDENTITY/SOUL - THERE ARE DIAGNOSTIC QUESTIONS AND DON'T RUSH FOR FIXES! CONFIRM ITS THERE AND IF NOT, MAKE THIS AN UNBREAKABLE LAW"}],"timestamp":1775909709575}}
{"type":"message","id":"70f8851d","parentId":"dedd25c2","timestamp":"2026-04-11T12:15:17.402Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_e65e4977-3b2f-4318-ae88-b46f316d2d3c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"diagnostic\\|rush to fix\\|acknowledge\\|don't fix\\|mistake\" /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/IDENTITY.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":65878,"output":131,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66009,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775909717402}}
